entries.meaning: In a manner similar to Acanthocephala. [First attested late 19th c.]
Any of parasitic intestinal worms comprising the phylum Acanthocephala. [First attested late 19th c.]
examples: Clearly acanthocephalans contain large amounts of lipid and possess enzyme systems for lipid metabolism (Filipponi et al., 1994; Weber et al., 1995); however, use of these lipid deposits in energy metabolism is yet to be demonstrated.
